    <string name="infoActivity_title">Info on Istentapp</string>
    <string name="infoActivity_message">Istentapp is composed by <i>\"Istèntu\"</i> + app.\n
The sardinian word istèntu comes from <i>\"istèntare\"</i>, which means waiting, being late, to waste time.\n
However <i>\"s\'istèntu\"</i> was a trick used by parents to keep their kids entertained, so that they won\'t create any problem: it consisted in sending the child (or the children) to a relative\'s house by telling the kids <i>\"go to aunt Maria and tell her to give you \"s\'istèntu\"\"</i>.\n
Istèntu means \"waste of time\" and the child, unfamiliar with the term, expects something material which will never come.\n
In fact, after a while (even several hours), between child\'s requests of giving him s\'istèntu and the corresponding aunt\'s answers \"wait, I\'m looking for it\", the woman will send his nephew/niece at his/her home saying: \"I don\'t have any, we\'ve run out of it"; at this point though, the child has already spent several hours away, allowing his parent to complete his commitment without any trouble.\n\n
I\'ve decided to use this name for both my origins and the fact that I think this is a tool that helps keeping any distraction away.
    </string>

